{"id":91876,"title":"[Knee pain of unknown origin after total knee prosthesis in a patient with chronic polyarthritis].","abstract":"Persistierende Schmerzen nach KTP sind ein häufiges Problem. Die häufigsten Differenzialdiagnosen sind eine aseptische Lockerung, Fehlorientierung der Komponenten oder ein implantatassoziierter Infekt. Retropatelläre Schmerzen sowie funktionelle oder psychosomatische Ursachen kommen infrage. Beim Rheumatiker sollte ein akuter Rheumaschub, sowie wie im vorliegenden Fall eine Insuffizienzfraktur ausgeschlossen werden. Die im MRI nachgewiesene Fraktur zeigt eine ungewöhnliche, bisher nicht beschriebene Lokalisation. Gelenknah empfiehlt sich zur Vermeidung von Funktionsverlusten eine operative Stabilisierung, die in der Regel zu einer raschen Abheilung führt.Persisting pain after TKA is a frequent problem. The most frequent differential diagnoses are aseptic loosening, malpositioning or a prosthetic joint infection. Retropatellar pain, functional or psychosomatic cause should be taken into account, too. An acute episode in patients with a rheumatoid arthritis should be ruled out. Insufficiency fractures, which can also be found in the presented case, are more often in patients with rheumatoid arthritis. The insufficiency fracture was detectable in the MRI and shows an uncommon, non-described localization. To prevent a loss of mobility of fractures close to the joint a surgical stabilizing is recommended, leading to quick healing. ","date":"2014-01-28","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24468456","annotations":[{"name":"Rheumatoid arthritis","weight":0.877494,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rheumatoid_arthritis"},{"name":"Magnetic resonance imaging","weight":0.796849,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnetic_resonance_imaging"},{"name":"Arthritis","weight":0.751806,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arthritis"},{"name":"Chronic (medicine)","weight":0.748573,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chronic_(medicine)"},{"name":"Knee","weight":0.735569,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knee"},{"name":"Joint","weight":0.735569,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joint"},{"name":"Differential diagnosis","weight":0.734035,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differential_diagnosis"},{"name":"Septic arthritis","weight":0.733635,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Septic_arthritis"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.728515,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Pain","weight":0.701843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pain"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.695164,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Fracture","weight":0.647429,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fracture"},{"name":"Acute (medicine)","weight":0.639348,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acute_(medicine)"},{"name":"Psychosomatic medicine","weight":0.57551,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychosomatic_medicine"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.57335,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Knee pain","weight":0.530486,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knee_pain"},{"name":"Prosthesis","weight":0.453086,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prosthesis"},{"name":"Asepsis","weight":0.364652,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asepsis"},{"name":"Polyarthritis","weight":0.268656,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polyarthritis"},{"name":"Healing","weight":0.200374,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Healing"},{"name":"Rheumatism","weight":0.144841,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rheumatism"},{"name":"Death","weight":0.0365852,"wikipedia_article":"http:/